gb15629dot11wapiMIB.name: gb15629dot11wapiMIB
gb15629dot11wapiMIB.organization: China Broadband Wireless IP Standard Group.
gb15629dot11wapiMIB.contactinfo: Contact: E-mail: bwips@chinabwips.org P.O.BOX 88, West High-tech Development Center, Xi'an, China. 710075 Tel: +86 29 8838 6220 Fax: +86 29 8838 6218

gb15629dot11wapiConfigTable.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigTable
gb15629dot11wapiConfigTable.description: The table containing WAPI configuration objects.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigVersion.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigVersion
gb15629dot11wapiConfigVersion.description: The highest WAPI version this entity supports.

gb15629dot11wapiControlledAuthControl.name: gb15629dot11wapiControlledAuthControl
gb15629dot11wapiControlledAuthControl.description: This object indicates whether the entity enables authentication. When the value is FALSE, it shall indicate that authentication is not enabled on this entity, and the status of the controlled port is 'authenticated'. When the value is TURE, it shall indicate that authentication is enabled, and the status of controlled port is decided by gb15629dot11wapiControlledPortControl.

gb15629dot11wapiControlledPortControl.name: gb15629dot11wapiControlledPortControl
gb15629dot11wapiControlledPortControl.description: This object indicates the controlling type of the entity's port. This object is available when gb15629dot11wapiControlledAuthControl is TURE. When the value is zero, it means 'automatic', and the status of the controlled port is decided by authentication result. When the value is one, it means 'forcible unauthenticated', and the status of the controlled port is 'unauthenticated'.

gb15629dot11wapiOptionImplemented.name: gb15629dot11wapiOptionImplemented
gb15629dot11wapiOptionImplemented.description: This object indicates whether the entity support WAPI. When the value is TURE, it shall indicate that the entity support WAPI. Otherwise, it shall indicate that the entity doesn't support WAPI.

gb15629dot11wapiPreauthenticationImpleme.name: gb15629dot11wapiPreauthenticationImplemented
gb15629dot11wapiPreauthenticationImpleme.description: This object indicates whether the entity support WAPI preauthentication. This object can't be set to TURE, unless gb15629dot11wapiOptionImplemented is TURE.

gb15629dot11wapiEnabled.name: gb15629dot11wapiEnabled
gb15629dot11wapiEnabled.description: When this object is set to TRUE, it shall indicate that WAPI is enabled on this entity. The entity will advertise the WAPI information element in its beacon and probe response frames.

gb15629dot11wapiPreauthenticationEnabled.name: gb15629dot11wapiPreauthenticationEnabled
gb15629dot11wapiPreauthenticationEnabled.description: When this object is set to TRUE, it shall indicate that WAPI preauthentication is enabled on this entity. Otherwise, it shall indicate that WAPI preauthentication is disabled on this entity. This object requires that gb15629dot11WAPIEnabled also be set to TRUE.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastKeysSupport.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastKeysSupported
gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastKeysSupport.description: This object indicates how many unicast keys the entity supports for WAPI.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastRekeyMethod.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastRekeyMethod
gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastRekeyMethod.description: This object selects a mechanism for rekeying the WAPI USK. The default is time-based, once per day. Rekeying the USK is only applicable to an entity acting as a role of AE or ASUE.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastRekeyTime.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastRekeyTime
gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastRekeyTime.description: The time in seconds after which the WAPI USK shall be refreshed. The timer shall start at the moment the USK was set using the MLME-SETWPIKEYS request primitive.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastRekeyPacket.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastRekeyPackets
gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastRekeyPacket.description: A packet count (in 1000s of packets) after which the WAPI USK shall be refreshed. The packet counter shall start at the moment the USK was set using the MLME-SETKEYS request primitive and it shall count all packets encrypted using the current USK.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigMulticastCipher.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigMulticastCipher
gb15629dot11wapiConfigMulticastCipher.description: This object indicates the multicast cipher suite selector the entity must use. The multicast cipher suite in the WAPI information element shall take its value from this variable. It consists of an OUI (the first 3 octets) and a cipher suite identifier (the last octet).

gb15629dot11wapiConfigMulticastRekeyMeth.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigMulticastRekeyMethod
gb15629dot11wapiConfigMulticastRekeyMeth.description: This object selects a mechanism for rekeying the WAPI MSK. The default is time-based, once per day. Rekeying the MSK is only applicable to an entity acting as a role of AE or ASUE.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigMulticastRekeyTime.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigMulticastRekeyTime
gb15629dot11wapiConfigMulticastRekeyTime.description: The time in seconds after which the WAPI MSK shall be refreshed. The timer shall start at the moment the MSK was set using the MLME-SETWPIKEYS request primitive.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigMulticastRekeyPack.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigMulticastRekeyPackets
gb15629dot11wapiConfigMulticastRekeyPack.description: A packet count (in 1000s of packets) after which the WAPI MSK shall be refreshed. The packet counter shall start at the moment the MSK was set using the MLME-SETKEYS request primitive and it shall count all packets encrypted using the current MSK.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigMulticastRekeyStri.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigMulticastRekeyStrict
gb15629dot11wapiConfigMulticastRekeyStri.description: This object signals that the MSK shall be refreshed whenever a STA leaves the BSS that possesses the MSK.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigPSKValue.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigPSKValue
gb15629dot11wapiConfigPSKValue.description: The PSK value when WAPI in PSK mode is the selected AKM suite. In that case, the BK will obtain its value from this object. This object is logically write-only. Reading this variable shall return unsuccessful status or null or zero.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigPSKPassPhrase.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigPSKPassPhrase
gb15629dot11wapiConfigPSKPassPhrase.description: The PSK value when WAPI in PSK mode is the selected AKM suite, is configured by gb15629dot11wapiConfigPSKValue. An alternative manner of setting the PSK uses the password-to-key algorithm. This variable provides a means to enter a pass-phrase. When this object is written, the WAPI entity shall use the password-to-key algorithm to derive a preshared and populate gb15629dot11wapiConfigPSKValue with this key. This object is logically write-only. Reading this variable shall return unsuccessful status or null or zero.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigCertificateUpdateC.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigCertificateUpdateCount
gb15629dot11wapiConfigCertificateUpdateC.description: The number of times message in the WAPI certificate authenticating handshake will be retried per certificate authenticating handshake attempt.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigMulticastUpdateCou.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigMulticastUpdateCount
gb15629dot11wapiConfigMulticastUpdateCou.description: The number of times message in the WAPI multicast key handshake will be retried per MSK handshake attempt.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastUpdateCount.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastUpdateCount
gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastUpdateCount.description: The number of times message in the WAPI unicast key handshake will be retried per 3-way handshake attempt.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigMulticastCipherSiz.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigMulticastCipherSize
gb15629dot11wapiConfigMulticastCipherSiz.description: This object indicates the length in bits of the multicast cipher key. This should be 256 for SMS4. first 128 bits for encrypting, last 128 bits for integrity checking.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigBKLifetime.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigBKLifetime
gb15629dot11wapiConfigBKLifetime.description: The maximum lifetime of a BK in the BK cache.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigBKReauthThreshold.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigBKReauthThreshold
gb15629dot11wapiConfigBKReauthThreshold.description: The percentage of the BK lifetime that should expire before an reauthentication occurs.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigSATimeout.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigSATimeout
gb15629dot11wapiConfigSATimeout.description: The maximum time a security association shall take to set up.

gb15629dot11wapiAuthenticationSuiteSelec.name: gb15629dot11wapiAuthenticationSuiteSelected
gb15629dot11wapiAuthenticationSuiteSelec.description: The selector of the last AKM suite negotiated.

gb15629dot11wapiUnicastCipherSelected.name: gb15629dot11wapiUnicastCipherSelected
gb15629dot11wapiUnicastCipherSelected.description: The selector of the last unicast cipher negotiated.

gb15629dot11wapiMulticastCipherSelected.name: gb15629dot11wapiMulticastCipherSelected
gb15629dot11wapiMulticastCipherSelected.description: The selector of the last multicast cipher negotiated.

gb15629dot11wapiBKIDUsed.name: gb15629dot11wapiBKIDUsed
gb15629dot11wapiBKIDUsed.description: The selector of the last BKID used in the last unicast cipher key handshake.

gb15629dot11wapiAuthenticationSuiteReque.name: gb15629dot11wapiAuthenticationSuiteRequested
gb15629dot11wapiAuthenticationSuiteReque.description: The selector of the last AKM suite requested.

gb15629dot11wapiUnicastCipherRequested.name: gb15629dot11wapiUnicastCipherRequested
gb15629dot11wapiUnicastCipherRequested.description: The selector of the last unicast cipher requested.

gb15629dot11wapiMulticastCipherRequested.name: gb15629dot11wapiMulticastCipherRequested
gb15629dot11wapiMulticastCipherRequested.description: The selector of the last multicast cipher requested.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastCiphersTabl.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastCiphersTable
gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastCiphersTabl.description: This table lists the unicast ciphers supported by this entity. It allows enabling and disabling of each unicast cipher by network management. The unicast cipher suite list in the WAPI information element is formed using the information in this table.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastCiphersEntr.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastCiphersEntry
gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastCiphersEntr.description: The table entry, indexed by the interface index (or all interfaces) and the unicast cipher.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastCipher.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastCipher
gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastCipher.description: The selector of a supported unicast cipher. It consists of an OUI(the first 3 octets) and a cipher suite identifier (the last octet).

gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastCipherEnabl.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastCipherEnabled
gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastCipherEnabl.description: This object enables or disables the unicast cipher.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastCipherSize.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastCipherSize
gb15629dot11wapiConfigUnicastCipherSize.description: This object indicates the length in bits of the unicast cipher key. This should be 256 for SMS4, first 128 bits for encrypting, last 128 bits for integrity checking.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigAuthenticationSuit.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigAuthenticationSuitesTable
gb15629dot11wapiConfigAuthenticationSuit.description: This table lists the AKM suites supported by this entity. Each AKM suite can be individually enabled and disabled. The AKM suite list in the WAPI information element is formed using the information in this table.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigAuthenticationSuit.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigAuthenticationSuiteIndex
gb15629dot11wapiConfigAuthenticationSuit.description: The auxiliary variable used as an index into the gb15629dot11wapiConfigAuthenticationSuitesTable.

gb15629dot11wapiConfigAuthenticationSuit.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigAuthenticationSuite
gb15629dot11wapiConfigAuthenticationSuit.description: The selector of an AKM suite. It consists of an OUI (the first 3 octets) and a cipher suite identifier (the last octet).

gb15629dot11wapiConfigAuthenticationSuit.name: gb15629dot11wapiConfigAuthenticationSuiteEnabled
gb15629dot11wapiConfigAuthenticationSuit.description: This variable indicates the corresponding AKM suite is enabled or disabled.

gb15629dot11wapiStatsTable.name: gb15629dot11wapiStatsTable
gb15629dot11wapiStatsTable.description: This table maintains per-STA statistics in an WAPI. The entry with gb15629dot11wapiStatsSTAAddress set to FF-FF-FF-FF-FF-FF shall contain statistics for broadcast/multicast traffic.

gb15629dot11wapiStatsIndex.name: gb15629dot11wapiStatsIndex
gb15629dot11wapiStatsIndex.description: An auxiliary index into the gb15629dot11wapiStatsTable.

gb15629dot11wapiStatsSTAAddress.name: gb15629dot11wapiStatsSTAAddress
gb15629dot11wapiStatsSTAAddress.description: The MAC address of the STA to which the statistics in this conceptual row belong.

gb15629dot11wapiStatsVersion.name: gb15629dot11wapiStatsVersion
gb15629dot11wapiStatsVersion.description: The WAPI version with which the STA associated.

gb15629dot11wapiStatsControlledPortStatu.name: gb15629dot11wapiStatsControlledPortStatus
gb15629dot11wapiStatsControlledPortStatu.description: This object indicates the status of the authentication entity's controlled port. When the value is TURE, it means 'authenticated'. Otherwise, it means 'unauthenticated'.

gb15629dot11wapiStatsSelectedUnicastCiph.name: gb15629dot11wapiStatsSelectedUnicastCipher
gb15629dot11wapiStatsSelectedUnicastCiph.description: The unicast cipher suite selector used during association.

gb15629dot11wapiStatsWPIReplayCounters.name: gb15629dot11wapiStatsWPIReplayCounters
gb15629dot11wapiStatsWPIReplayCounters.description: The number of WPI MPDUs discarded by the replay mechanism.

gb15629dot11wapiStatsWPIDecryptableError.name: gb15629dot11wapiStatsWPIDecryptableErrors
gb15629dot11wapiStatsWPIDecryptableError.description: The number of WPI MPDUs discarded because of unavailable cipher key when WPI-SMS4 decrypting.

gb15629dot11wapiStatsWPIMICErrors.name: gb15629dot11wapiStatsWPIMICErrors
gb15629dot11wapiStatsWPIMICErrors.description: The number of WPI MPDUs discarded because of MIC checking failure when WPI-SMS4 decrypting.

gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAISignatureErrors.name: gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAISignatureErrors
gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAISignatureErrors.description: This counter increases when the received WAI packets' signature is wrong.

gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAIHMACErrors.name: gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAIHMACErrors
gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAIHMACErrors.description: This counter increases when the received WAI packets' message authentication key checking error occurs.

gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAIAuthenticationRe.name: gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAIAuthenticationResultFailures
gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAIAuthenticationRe.description: This counter increases when the WAI authentication result is unsuccessful.

gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAIDiscardCounters.name: gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAIDiscardCounters
gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAIDiscardCounters.description: This counter increases when the received WAI packet is discarded.

gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAITimeoutCounters.name: gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAITimeoutCounters
gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAITimeoutCounters.description: This counter increases when the WAI packet overtime is detected.

gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAIFormatErrors.name: gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAIFormatErrors
gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAIFormatErrors.description: This counter increases when the WAI packets' format error occurs

gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAICertificateHands.name: gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAICertificateHandshakeFailures
gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAICertificateHands.description: This counter increases when the WAI certificate authenticates unsuccessfully.

gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAIUnicastHandshake.name: gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAIUnicastHandshakeFailures
gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAIUnicastHandshake.description: This counter increases when the WAI unicast cipher key negotiates unsuccessfully.

gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAIMulticastHandsha.name: gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAIMulticastHandshakeFailures
gb15629dot11wapiStatsWAIMulticastHandsha.description: This counter increases when the WAI multicast cipher key announces unsuccessfully.

gb15629dot11wapiBase.name: gb15629dot11wapiBase
gb15629dot11wapiBase.description: The gb15629dot11wapiBase object class provides the necessary support for managing WAPI functionality in the STA.

gb15629dot11wapiBKcachingGroup.name: gb15629dot11wapiBKcachingGroup
gb15629dot11wapiBKcachingGroup.description: The gb15629dot11wapiBKcachingGroup object class provides the necessary support for managing BK caching functionality in the STA

gb15629dot11wapiCompliance.name: gb15629dot11wapiCompliance
gb15629dot11wapiCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMPv2 entities that implement the WAPI MIB.
